social_posts.post_text:
“Throw kindness around like confetti” 

I’ve been getting two questions a lot from my former yoga students. 
Is law school as hard as they say?
YES. 
Do you still practice yoga?
yes.
It just isn’t always handstands everyday and I’m cool with that. 

As we are having our spring break I just wanted to lay out an enormous thank you to everyone who knows what a heavy lift this is and have truly helped me stay grounded. Here in Vermont, the collective kindness of strangers who aren’t strangers anymore, continues to remind me what a good idea this was. 
In yoga we talk about the power of breath. Acknowledging the inhale as energy taken in and the exhale as it’s natural balance. 
So gonna embrace a week of the exhale. 
Look for those moments when you can. 
#gratitude

I’d “move mountains” for….♥️
I thought about that phrase today. I think it means to believe that the impossible IS possible, that we are not the limitations we see in ourselves, but instead just expanding what we believe. It kinda goes with motherhood for sure. And now this year my son has 💯 had faith in me in going back to school. We will both be graduating class of ‘25, him in Georgia me in Vermont. Seriously I am a lucky mom. To all those who have had a climb this year. Happy Mother’s Day.

#lawschoolrequiresyoga
Also got myself a new yoga mat, as my last one biodegraded appropriately after 4 years of daily use. For all my fellow yoga nerds out there, this is an official unofficial endorsement of @liforme. 
Yes they are boujee but it is a certified B Corp sustainable brand and an excellent mat. 💕
And for my fellow law students maybe not a new yoga mat, but do something nice for yourself as the mid semester madness continues. 🙃
